most sensitive to time horizon, the relative utility weights of successful 
ablation versus unsuccessful drug therapy, and to the cost of an ablation 
procedure.
CONCLUSIONS: RFA with/without AAD for symptomatic, drug-refractory paroxysmal AF 
appears to be reasonably cost-effective compared with AAD therapy alone from the 
perspective of the US health care system, based on improved quality of life and 
avoidance of future health care costs.

