Parkinson's disease is one of the most common and debilitating movement 
disorders. It affects a large number of the aging population and as the life 
expectancy of the average person increases, it will affect ever increasing 
numbers of people. Diagnostic accuracy remains problematic and treatment for 
some is unsatisfactory. New understanding of the mechanism behind 
