availability and tissue distribution of iron load. Intensive chelation regimens 
combining L1 and DFO are recommended in patients with cardiac complications, 
while DFRA has been found to be effective in reducing serum ferritin, with 
acceptable side effects. Here, we report advances in thalassemia treatment in 
Taiwan and suggest treatment guidelines.

